		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Here is the palette for the first BG layer.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">BG palette 2:<br />rgb(0,0,0)<br />rgb(0,10,6)<br />rgb(0,21,8)<br />rgb(8,28,9)<br />rgb(21,31,15)<br />rgb(0,0,0)<br />rgb(6,0,3)<br />rgb(13,1,4)<br />rgb(20,5,5)<br />rgb(26,12,5)<br />rgb(31,20,5)<br />rgb(0,3,6)<br />rgb(0,7,11)<br />rgb(3,13,18)<br />rgb(8,21,24)<br />rgb(17,28,30)<br /><br />BG palette 3:<br />rgb(0,0,0)<br />rgb(0,0,0)<br />rgb(0,0,0)<br />rgb(0,0,0)<br />rgb(0,0,0)<br />rgb(0,0,0)<br />rgb(21,0,0)<br />rgb(27,6,0)<br />rgb(31,13,0)<br />rgb(31,21,0)<br />rgb(31,27,6)<br />rgb(18,8,6)<br />rgb(25,16,12)<br />rgb(29,23,18)<br />rgb(30,27,23)<br />rgb(31,31,27)<br /></div><br /><br />BG palettes 0 and 1 are reserved for BG3.

		

