	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I haven't used GIMP in a while, but I remember testing animations with it. IIRC, each animation frame is a layer, and you can specify delays and other parameters using the layer's name. Then you can just go to Filters -&gt; Animation -&gt; Playback to see the animation. Do you need more than that?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
