	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Tile set for Alisha's Adventure</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes GIMP has very minimal support for animated GIFs, and there is a playback tool. It is very rudimentary, and awkward to use. A real animation tool is light years beyond this, really.<br /><br />Aseprite lets you switch frames with a keypress, use several layers each animated separately (GIMP is using layers in lieu of real frames, preventing this possibility), easily change speeds and partial loops, onion skin to trace over previous frames, etc. etc.<br /><br />There's really no comparison. GIMP's animated GIF support is a just barely working hack. Aseprite is designed around the task of animation.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


